keyFacts: Jeffrey Epstein sent an email on October 23, 2010, with a subject line containing the phrases 'spenet time with daddy' and 'great fun'.
The email includes a confidentiality notice claiming the communication may be attorney-client privileged and constitutes inside information.
The notice states the information is the property of Jeffrey Epstein and warns against unauthorized use, disclosure, or copying.
The document is explicitly marked as subject to a protective order covering specific paragraphs (7, 8, 9, 10, 15, and 17).
